<paragraph blockId="17.[530,838,249,276]" box="[530,838,249,276]" pageId="17">
<heading box="[530,838,249,276]" centered="true" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="17" reason="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[530,705,249,276]" italics="true" pageId="17">
<taxonomicName authority="Borkent, 2019" authorityName="Borkent" authorityYear="2019" box="[530,699,249,276]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Gerontodacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="new genus">Gerontodacus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[713,838,250,276]" pageId="17" rank="genus">new genus</taxonomicNameLabel>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[180,1079,300,327]" pageId="17" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="17.[132,1237,300,1335]" box="[180,1079,300,327]" pageId="17">
<typeStatus box="[180,239,301,327]" pageId="17">TYPE</typeStatus>
SPECIES: 
<taxonomicName authority="(Szadziewski)" authorityName="Szadziewski" baseAuthorityName="Szadziewski" baseAuthorityYear="1996" box="[354,798,300,327]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Gerontodacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="succineus">
<emphasis box="[354,629,300,326]" italics="true" pageId="17">Gerontodacus succineus</emphasis>
(Szadziewski)
</taxonomicName>
by present designation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="17.[132,1237,300,1335]" pageId="17">
DIAGNOSIS: The only Cretaceous genus of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Szadziewski" authorityYear="1996" box="[698,902,337,363]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Ceratopogonidae</taxonomicName>
without R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1033,1063,351,368]" fontSize="7" pageId="17">4+5</subScript>
, with 2 radial cells, r-m oblique to R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[398,407,388,405]" fontSize="7" pageId="17">1</subScript>
(fig. 6B)
<subScript attach="left" box="[513,517,389,405]" fontSize="7" pageId="17">,</subScript>
an elongate anapleural suture (as in fig. 1A), a foreleg tarsal ratio/hind-leg tarsal ratio ≤ 1.3, and fore- and midtrochanter each lacking a pair of thick setae. To further distinguish 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Borkent" authorityYear="2019" box="[399,558,449,475]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Gerontodacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[399,558,449,475]" italics="true" pageId="17">Gerontodacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
females from those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boesel" authorityYear="1937" box="[829,1001,449,475]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Protoculicoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[829,1001,449,475]" italics="true" pageId="17">Protoculicoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Borkent" authorityYear="2019" box="[1016,1175,449,475]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Gerontodacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1016,1175,449,475]" italics="true" pageId="17">Gerontodacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a squat, semispherical antennal pedicel (fig. 4F, G) while those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boesel" authorityYear="1937" box="[899,1071,487,513]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Protoculicoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[899,1071,487,513]" italics="true" pageId="17">Protoculicoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have an elongate pedicel (figs. 1B, C, 2B, 4D).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[132,1237,300,1335]" pageId="17">
REMARKS: Aside from the 
<typeStatus box="[508,559,562,588]" pageId="17">type</typeStatus>
species, there are three further species included in the genus, as follows: 
<taxonomicName authority="(Choufani, Azar, and Nel)" authorityName="Borkent" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Choufani, Azar, and Nel" baseAuthorityYear="2019" box="[356,861,599,626]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Gerontodacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="krzeminskii" status="new combination">
<emphasis box="[356,528,599,625]" italics="true" pageId="17">G. krzeminskii</emphasis>
(Choufani, Azar, and Nel)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[877,1090,599,625]" pageId="17" rank="species">new combination</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Borkent)" authorityName="Borkent" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Borkent" baseAuthorityYear="2000" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Gerontodacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctus" status="new combination">
<emphasis box="[1106,1236,599,625]" italics="true" pageId="17">G. punctus</emphasis>
(Borkent)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[261,469,636,663]" pageId="17" rank="species">new combination</taxonomicNameLabel>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Szadziewski and Arillo)" authorityName="Borkent" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Szadziewski and Arillo" baseAuthorityYear="2019" box="[534,952,636,663]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Gerontodacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="skalskii" status="new combination">
<emphasis box="[534,652,636,663]" italics="true" pageId="17">G. skalskii</emphasis>
(Szadziewski and Arillo)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[965,1173,636,663]" pageId="17" rank="species">new combination</taxonomicNameLabel>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[132,1237,300,1335]" pageId="17">
The 
<typeStatus box="[232,283,674,700]" pageId="17">type</typeStatus>
species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Szadziewski" baseAuthorityName="Szadziewski" baseAuthorityYear="1996" box="[389,532,674,700]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Gerontodacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="succineus">
<emphasis box="[389,532,674,700]" italics="true" pageId="17">G. succineus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, has plesiomorphic conditions that exclude it from the lineage defined by synapomorphies 11’, 12–13, has synapomorphies 6–7 and lacks synapomorphy 8 (fig. 10) and is here stated to be the 
<typeStatus box="[599,650,749,775]" pageId="17">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Borkent" authorityYear="2019" box="[784,943,748,774]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Gerontodacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[784,943,748,774]" italics="true" pageId="17">Gerontodacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Although the character states 9, 11’, 12–13 could not be examined for 
<taxonomicName authority="(Choufani, Azar, and Nel)" authorityName="Borkent" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Choufani, Azar, and Nel" baseAuthorityYear="2019" box="[698,1194,785,812]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Gerontodacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="krzeminskii">
<emphasis box="[698,868,785,812]" italics="true" pageId="17">G. krzeminskii</emphasis>
(Choufani, Azar, and Nel)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Borkent" baseAuthorityName="Borkent" baseAuthorityYear="2000" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Gerontodacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17">G. punctus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Szadziewski and Arillo)" authorityName="Borkent" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Szadziewski and Arillo" baseAuthorityYear="2019" box="[295,727,823,850]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Gerontodacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="skalskii">
<emphasis box="[295,417,823,849]" italics="true" pageId="17">G. skalskii</emphasis>
(Szadziewski and Arillo)
</taxonomicName>
, these species are placed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Borkent" authorityYear="2019" box="[1076,1236,823,849]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Gerontodacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1076,1236,823,849]" italics="true" pageId="17">Gerontodacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because of overall similarity to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Szadziewski" baseAuthorityName="Szadziewski" baseAuthorityYear="1996" box="[511,656,861,887]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Gerontodacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="succineus">
<emphasis box="[511,656,861,887]" italics="true" pageId="17">G. succineus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. They lack synapomorphy 8 and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Borkent" baseAuthorityName="Borkent" baseAuthorityYear="2000" box="[1060,1187,861,887]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Gerontodacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctus">
<emphasis box="[1060,1187,861,887]" italics="true" pageId="17">G. punctus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has synapomorphy 7 (males are unknown for the other two species). There is no synapomorphy indicating the monophyly of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Borkent" authorityYear="2019" box="[476,635,935,961]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Gerontodacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[476,635,935,961]" italics="true" pageId="17">Gerontodacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. As such the placement of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Borkent" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Choufani, Azar, and Nel" baseAuthorityYear="2019" box="[954,1121,935,961]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Gerontodacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="krzeminskii">
<emphasis box="[954,1121,935,961]" italics="true" pageId="17">G. krzeminskii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Borkent" baseAuthorityName="Borkent" baseAuthorityYear="2000" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Gerontodacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17">G. punctus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Borkent" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Szadziewski and Arillo" baseAuthorityYear="2019" box="[236,356,972,999]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Gerontodacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="skalskii">
<emphasis box="[236,356,972,999]" italics="true" pageId="17">G. skalskii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is tenuous. Likewise, it is possible that with further analysis the nontype species will be recognized as further distinct lineages within this region of the phylogeny.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[132,1237,300,1335]" pageId="17">
Recent examination of Burmese amber reveals that at least one unnamed species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Borkent" authorityYear="2019" box="[132,292,1084,1110]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Gerontodacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[132,292,1084,1110]" italics="true" pageId="17">Gerontodacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is present.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[132,1237,300,1335]" pageId="17">
BIONOMIC INFORMATION: The details of the mouthparts of only one species were evident (
<bibRefCitation author="Borkent, A." box="[140,327,1159,1185]" pageId="17" pagination="355 - 451" refId="ref23310" refString="Borkent, A. 2000 a. Biting midges (Ceratopogonidae: Diptera) from Lower Cretaceous Lebanese amber with a discussion of the diversity and patterns found in other ambers. In D. Grimaldi (editor), Studies on fossils in amber, with particular reference to the Cretaceous of New Jersey: 355 - 451. Leiden: Backhuys Publishers." type="book chapter" year="2000">Borkent, 2000a</bibRefCitation>
). The presence of fine mandibular teeth and retrorse lacinial teeth indicates that at least female 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Borkent" baseAuthorityName="Borkent" baseAuthorityYear="2000" box="[370,497,1197,1223]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Gerontodacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctus">
<emphasis box="[370,497,1197,1223]" italics="true" pageId="17">G. punctus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
fed on vertebrate blood (
<bibRefCitation author="Borkent, A." box="[808,983,1196,1223]" pageId="17" refId="ref23213" refString="Borkent, A. 1995. Biting midges in the Cretaceous amber of North America (Diptera: Ceratopogonidae). Leiden: Backhuys Publishers." type="book" year="1995">Borkent, 1995</bibRefCitation>
). The well-developed male antennal plume of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Szadziewski" baseAuthorityName="Szadziewski" baseAuthorityYear="1996" box="[412,552,1234,1260]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Gerontodacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="succineus">
<emphasis box="[412,552,1234,1260]" italics="true" pageId="17">G. succineus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Borkent" baseAuthorityName="Borkent" baseAuthorityYear="2000" box="[609,732,1234,1260]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Gerontodacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctus">
<emphasis box="[609,732,1234,1260]" italics="true" pageId="17">G. punctus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
indicates that, similar to most 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Szadziewski" authorityYear="1996" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Ceratopogonidae</taxonomicName>
, the males formed mating swarms.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[180,969,1308,1335]" pageId="17" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="17.[132,1237,300,1335]" box="[180,969,1308,1335]" pageId="17">
ETYMOLOGY: from the Greek 
<emphasis box="[531,594,1309,1334]" italics="true" pageId="17">geron</emphasis>
(“old one”) and 
<emphasis box="[791,857,1308,1334]" italics="true" pageId="17">dacus</emphasis>
(“biter”).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
